sh chain. Source: summary.recently_exited, family(261617).\u001b[0m                           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mTwo active ./godshell binaries are present, both launched interactively from shells, so they look operator-started.\u001b[m           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mEvidence: PID 261617 binary_path ./godshell under sh(261530), uptime 31s; PID 250968 binary_path ./godshell under zsh -\u001b[m       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mi(9500), uptime 48m. Both read /home/raul/.config/godshell/config.json and made a few connections to 1.1.1.1:853. Source:\u001b[m     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204minspect(261617), inspect(250968), family.\u001b[0m                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mAntigravity’s language server is noisy and data-heavy but appears workspace-related, not covert by itself. Evidence: PID\u001b[m      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m4402 has very high memory 1084072 KB and many outbound HTTPS connections to Google/GitHub/Cloudfront plus repeated opens in\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m/home/raul/Desktop/projects/godshell and ~/.gemini/antigravity files; command line explicitly names workspace_id\u001b[m              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mfile_home_raul_Desktop_projects_godshell and cloud endpoint daily-cloudcode-pa.googleapis.com. Source: inspect(4402),\u001b[m         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mfamily(250968), summary.\u001b[0m                                                                                                      \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mI do not see a currently active unknown persistence implant from this snapshot. Absence evidence: no rogue parentless\u001b[m         \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mbinary, no hidden child tree off init beyond normal desktop apps, and the obviously malicious commands are in shell history\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mas lab activity. Source: summary, family, inspect.\u001b[0m                 "]
